## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-395">O elemento curinga é adicionado ao final da sequência atual de elementos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-395">The wildcard element is added to the end of the current sequence of elements.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-396">O elemento curinga corresponde a qualquer palavra falada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-396">The wildcard element matches any spoken word.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-397">Ele não coincide com ruídos de fundo ou silêncio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-397">It does not match background noise or silence.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-398">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática que aceita a entrada de senha como um caractere curinga.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-398">The following example creates a grammar that accepts password input as a wildcard.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-399">O exemplo anexa um <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> manipulador de eventos a gramática que valida a entrada de senha.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-399">The example attaches a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> event handler to the grammar that validates the password input.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
private Grammar CreatePasswordGrammar()  
{  
  GrammarBuilder wildcardBuilder = new GrammarBuilder();  
  wildcardBuilder.AppendWildcard();  
  SemanticResultKey passwordKey =  
    new SemanticResultKey("Password", wildcardBuilder);  
  
  GrammarBuilder passwordBuilder =  
    new GrammarBuilder("My Password is");  
  passwordBuilder.Append(passwordKey);  
  
  Grammar passwordGrammar = new Grammar(passwordBuilder);  
  passwordGrammar.Name = "Password input";  
  
  passwordGrammar.SpeechRecognized +=  
    new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(  
      PasswordInputHandler);  
  
  return passwordGrammar;  
}  
  
// Handle the SpeechRecognized event for the password grammar.  
private void PasswordInputHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  RecognitionResult result = e.Result;  
  SemanticValue semantics = e.Result.Semantics;  
  
  if (semantics.ContainsKey("Password"))  
  {  
    RecognizedAudio passwordAudio =  
      result.GetAudioForWordRange(  
        result.Words[3], result.Words[result.Words.Count - 1]);  
  
    if (IsValidPassword(passwordAudio))  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Password accepted.");  
  
      // Add code to handle a valid password here.  
    }  
    else  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Invalid password.");  
  
      // Add code to handle an invalid password here.  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
// Validate the password input.   
private bool IsValidPassword(RecognizedAudio passwordAudio)  
{  
  Console.WriteLine("Validating password.");  
  
  // Add password validation code here.  
  
  return false;  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-403">O <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> construtor cria um <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objeto que pode ser usado por um reconhecedor de fala da cultura correspondente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-403">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> constructor creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object that can be used by a speech recognizer of the corresponding culture.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-404">Somente o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Culture%2A> propriedade o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> que é fornecido como parâmetro para o construtor de gramática é usado para definir a cultura da gramática de reconhecimento de fala resultante.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-404">Only the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Culture%2A> property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> that is provided as the parameter to the Grammar constructor is used to set the culture of the resulting speech recognition grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-405">Microsoft Windows e a API Speech aceitar todos os códigos de país de idioma válidos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-405">Microsoft Windows and the System.Speech API accept all valid language-country codes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-406">Para executar o reconhecimento de fala usando o idioma especificado no `Culture` propriedade, um mecanismo de reconhecimento de fala que dá suporte a que o código do país de idioma deve ser instalado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-406">To perform speech recognition using the language specified in the `Culture` property, a speech recognition engine that supports that language-country code must be installed.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-407">Os mecanismos de reconhecimento de fala fornecido com o Microsoft Windows 7 trabalhar com os seguintes códigos de país de idioma.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-407">The speech recognition engines that shipped with Microsoft Windows 7 work with the following language-country codes.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-408">en-GB.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-408">en-GB.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-409">Inglês (Reino Unido)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-409">English (United Kingdom)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-410">en-US.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-410">en-US.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-411">Inglês (Estados Unidos)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-411">English (United States)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-412">de-DE.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-412">de-DE.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-413">Alemão (Alemanha)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-413">German (Germany)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-414">es-ES.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-414">es-ES.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-415">Espanhol (Espanha)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-415">Spanish (Spain)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-416">fr-FR.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-416">fr-FR.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-417">Francês (França)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-417">French (France)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-418">ja-JP.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-418">ja-JP.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-419">Japonês (Japão)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-419">Japanese (Japan)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-420">zh-CN.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-420">zh-CN.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="edfcc-421">Chinês (China)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="edfcc-421">Chinese (China)</span></span>  
  
